So much of a problem that I would literally stand in front of a blue/light blue and let it pound me into oblivion in hopes that my defense would go up, no dice.  I'm seriously thinking my character is bugged.. all my other skills go up.  Dodge goes up all the time .. but defense will not.  My armour class is really suffering, and I'm clueless as to how to fix it.  Any advice from anyone out there?  <br><br> <p>k thx la~<br>Love, <br>Ollias, The Captain's Avatar <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272718" target="_blank">Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elytaofthepride>Elyta of the Pride</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:02:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from my FV collegues</span><hr size=1> I find it goes up really quickly if you have two or more mobs on you at the same time  (less life expectancy though....) <p><b>Elyta</b><Br><i>Gnome Illusionist</i><Br><i>Member of the </i><a href=http://www.messages.tinkerspride.com>Tinker's Pride</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoliiasmoorglade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OliiasMoorglade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:07:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thephosphorbox.com/cptrply-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from my FV collegues</span><hr size=1> I suppose I could try that, I'd more than likely have to exchange 5 or so levels of xp in order to get the defense skill up to par though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>k thx la~<br>Love, <br>Ollias, The Captain's Avatar <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272718" target="_blank">Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaritzia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maritzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Uptight Cleric</span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:09:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from my FV collegues</span><hr size=1> Ollias, what's your current defense skill?  It's capped pretty low for clerics, and mine hasn't gone up hardly at all since just after my 20th season.  Anyone know what defense is capped at for clerics?<br><br> <p>Maritzia Soulhealer<br>29th Season Cleric of Rodcet Nife<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoliiasmoorglade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OliiasMoorglade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:15:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thephosphorbox.com/cptrply-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from my FV collegues</span><hr size=1> I really don't know the number, honestly it hasn't gone up in so long I would say it's probably in the neigborhood of 20-30 maybe?  Could even be lower than that. Like I said, I tried standing in front of a blue and letting it pretty much beat me to death, rooted it, healed to full, let it beat me again and repeated that until my mana was depleted over and over and it NEVER goes up.  Literally never.  Ever.  My dodge will go up a few points, but never defense.<br><br> <p>k thx la~<br>Love, <br>Ollias, The Captain's Avatar <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272718" target="_blank">Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:16:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> Your defense is really low. I don't know the exact number, but I wouldn't be surprised if it wasn't something like 210. <br><br><br>Don't sweat it. You're a cleric. If you get hit, you can blame it on the tanks for not controlling aggro (you could blame yourself for not controlling your heals, and their aggro, but I find it much easier to blame someone else =p)<br><br>-Krazak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usantix247.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santix247</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:20:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> Actually for a cleric its 200. Post 50 200 as well.<br> When you say your defense is low, how low is it? I mean are we talking 100 or 10?<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoliiasmoorglade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OliiasMoorglade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:21:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thephosphorbox.com/cptrply-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> I wish I could take that view on it Kraz <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Fact of the matter is, with the low defense it makes it really tough to cast through a beating even with my maxxed channelling skill..  <p>k thx la~<br>Love, <br>Ollias, The Captain's Avatar <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272718" target="_blank">Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=farnoak>Farnoak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:24:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> Go talk to a shaman and get your agility buffed.  If you're base Agility is sub 70 (like for an Erudite), your chances for skill ups are gonna be few and far between.<br><br>Even then, it's a slow process.  Agility impacts defensive skillup success rates the same way that Dexterity impacts weapon/offensive skillups and Intelligence/Wisdom impacts casting/learning skillups.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:26:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some advice from my FV collegues</span><hr size=1> Cleric defense is capped at 200 both pre- and post-50 (according to castersrealm). Assuming it follows the usual progression, your max is probably 5 points per level, and it'll cap at level 40. So your max defense should <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> probably</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be around 105 now.<br><br>Defense is probably the hardest skill to raise though. And the higher it gets the harder it seems to be to increase it more. In my 40s, still trying to catch up to my max defense of 210 (warrior pre-50 cap), I'd be lucky to get 2 points in a whole level. And that's a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> warrior</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I get pounded on all the time. So uh... just keep at it is all I can say. Oh, and try to get a dex buff. High dex seems to help with skill increases. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubormwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:26:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> I have found, although it may just be coincidence, that defensive abilities (parry, dodge, defense, etc) go up much faster with non-animal creatures hitting me. For example 2-3 orcs at a time will generally result in an increase while a similar battle with pumas will not. Perhaps it has something to do with weapon usage by the NPC, perhaps I am just not paying close enough attention.<br><br>Borm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoliiasmoorglade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OliiasMoorglade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:27:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thephosphorbox.com/cptrply-small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> My agility is currently 72, just above that 70 cutoff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p>k thx la~<br>Love, <br>Ollias, The Captain's Avatar <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=272718" target="_blank">Magelo!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uburanmcmuffin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BuranMcMuffin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:31:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> ooc: Its funny that you should mention this...<br><br>Poppyseed and Buran are both 12th level monks who fight together. We have almost identical stats and equipment, and take turns with aggro, so we get pounded on equally. Despite this, until about 10th level, Buran had about 30 points higher hand-to-hand, while Poppy's defense was about 30 points higher.<br><br>I tried to get Buran's defense to raise up by taking more of the aggro, tried pulling multiple mobs, etc. Nothing worked... And then, all of a sudden, over the course of the last few days, everything has pretty much evened out.<br><br>Soo... I suggest, like Krazak said, dont sweat it. If you have a healer friend and not much else to do, you could try meleeing with a few light blues to get your skill to increase. [The apes outside of Dalnir dont train and dont hit hard *at all* by level 29; even a cleric with poor defense could stand up to them with a little backup healing.] <br><br>It's not going to go up if you dont get hit, obviously, but you may have to take a bit of a beating before it starts to move.<br><br>Buran McMuffin, the original Iron Chef<br>**Slayin gnolls n makin muffins since 3174** <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 223<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:39:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1>      The magic number for AGI is 75 not 70. Get it there then get beat on alot, but as a cleric it is hard to keep it maxxed out if you have good pets (tanks). Mine is about 150 at the moment and slowly going up. I have also noticed skillups seem to go faster on mobs that just went blue and non-animal mobs. The non-animal mob thing could just be wishfull thinking though.<br> <p>Lexxi Ledenyetz<BR>42nd Prayer<BR>Cleric of Brell<BR>Ak'Anon<BR>Heiress and Officer of the Ledenyetz Troupe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 855<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 1:55:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> Hail brother.<br>There is a little known bug that can happen to your data file, when this bug happens you are buggered defense wise <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Once upon a time I play a mage, iris a necro. She got hit 3 to 4 times more than me and yet her defense was at about 12 by the time she was 20 :-) mine on the other hand was maxed.<br><br>We tried all kinds of things, in the end we spoke to a GM who fixed her, of course she was still lvl 20 with a defense cap of 12 but hey it went up now.<br><br>So contact a GM see if they can fix you ;-)<br><br>If you want the safe way of bringing up your defense cap go to an arena with a mage necro enchanter or shaman. Get there pet to smack you around :-) Insreases defense caps nicely <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Agi increases the rate at which you learn defensive skills so get some agi buffs first :-)<br><br>Good luck brother<br><br>Hugs<br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198034">Intra</A> and <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157327">Sena</A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/useaghankai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seaghan Kai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering the Lost Highway</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:00:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.comixtreme.com/Marvel/Ultimate%20Marvel/headshots/jackrussell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> I knew someone with the same bug Arios mentioned.  She contacted a GM and they were able to correct it.  So I would also suggest that, or let a couple of blues beat on you for awhile (with a back up healer, of course).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src="http://chuma.cas.usf.edu/~dking3/Seaghan_Druid.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=grumgor>Grumgor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 