ound waiting for tanks to get wailed on (LOL).<br><br> <p>Maritzia Soulhealer<br>29th Season Cleric of Rodcet Nife<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 394<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:57:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ok...</span><hr size=1> I am a defense junkie, all my characters have had max for level always.  <br><br><br>Priest classes max at 200 with lvl *5 being the cap.  At 20 the cap is 100 at 40 you are capped forever at 200.  You will have a naked unbuffed ac of 546 with 200 defence as a cleric. This means each and every point of defence is equal to 2.73 points.  until level 40 keeping defence maxed is like putting on a 9 ac raw (13 ac worn) piece of armor without taking up a slot.<br><br>Things that make for faster skill raises:<br><br>1) Agility:  Over 75 is good, over 105 is better, over 150 helps even more.  Find a shaman or ranger to give you an agi buff, maybe even buy some gear to swap in and out.<br><br>2) After lvl 10 it is very very difficult to get skill ups from light blues.  you need to find blues that hit fast for low damage and that you can control with root.<br><br>3) Keep your ac as high as you can with worn gear.  Make sure to train dodge if you haven't.  Alot of points will show up when a monster misses you or you dodge.<br><br>4) Solo.  You may not get much experience, but the first part of every level either solo or get a friend to look out for you while you take on some blues on your own.<br><br>5) last ditch measures include letting ping fuzzlecutter in Freeport whack on you while you heal yourself (try this after 40 and zone when lom, don't kill him unless faction is not an issue), also you can duel a pet class and let their blue pet hit you as well. <br> <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Tradesman, Polyglot and Drunken Alchemist <br>Proud member of Lux Aeternam</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveganus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veganus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:58:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Defense</span><hr size=1> I had Defense at 12 at level 27 as a soloing (root/nuke/root breaks and die) Wizard, then i got my 13th point and it shooted up, that happens.<br><br>The best you can do is to get Agi 75, that will help a lot to raise defense <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=2229.topic&start=21&stop=28>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2229.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2229.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2229.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=2229.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif borde